PREREQUISITE

- Vcftools (http://sourceforge.net/projects/vcftools/)

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	sudo ./install.sh

SAMPLE USAGE

The sample command to add new variant frequency from the input in vcf format into the database

	./bin/bvd-add.pl -d example/sample_DB example/sample_input.vcf

The sample command to retrieve the variant frequency

	./bin/bvd-get.pl -d example/sample_DB

Please note that the database that was used in the above commands, 'example/sample_DB', is for tutorial purpose only.
Practically, you can insert variant into the database by only

	./bin/bvd-add.pl your_input.vcf

and can retrieve the variant frequency by only

	./bin/bvd-get.pl

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find more information about this these tools in 

	hbvdb-tools.pdf

and you can find the library documentation at for this module by using perldoc command.

	perldoc Bvdb

